==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*marha-'', from Indo-European ''*marko-'' ‘horse’.  Cognate with Old Frisian [[merie]], Old Saxon [[merge]] (Dutch [[merrie]]), Old High German [[meriha]] ‘mare’ (German [[Mähre]]), Old Norse [[merr]], [[marr]] (Swedish [[märr]]).  The IE root is also the source of Irish [[marc]], Welsh [[march]] ‘horse’.

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /mæarh/

===Noun===
'''mearh''' ''m'' (''pl'' '''mēares''')
# a [[horse]], [[steed]]

